ratings.comment: He does pretty good for being a young guy without much experience. I recommend that other landscape architecture majors take him.
He's helpful and related abstract content to everyday stuff. Wanted participation. Made lecture as interactive as possible. Has open office hours.

Matt is fair, clear with expectations, and very willing to help during office hours. He is easy-going and entertaining. Not to mention easy on the eyes. The only downside is that ALL discussions must be attended (even if sick), otherwise a percentage point docked from final grade. :/ Awesome when you have swine flu.

Matt is my favorite TA on campus, and I've been here for four years. He's funny, knowledgable and super-helpful. He's from Wisocnsin, and can actually relate to students unlike some other people on campus.
